headline.main: Anchorage Cheers Dog Sled Teams in Ceremonial Start of Alaska's Iditarod
headline.print_headline: Anchorage Cheers Dog Sled Teams in Ceremonial Start of Alaska's Iditarod

lead_paragraph: Dozens of sled-dog teams glided through the frigid streets of Anchorage on Saturday in the ceremonial start to the Iditarod, a nearly 1,000-mile (1,610-km) sled dog race across the Alaskan wilderness and one of the world's most celebrated tests of endurance.
